joeonit Here's a working hammerspoon script, using the 'swipe.spoon' module from my previous comment. It works great - it's a four finger swipe to change workspaces.\n\n```lua\nSwipe = hs.loadSpoon(\"Swipe\")\n\nlocal AEROSPACE = \"/opt/homebrew/bin/aerospace\"\n\nfunction aerospaceExec(cmd)\n  os.execute(\"nohup \" .. AEROSPACE .. \" \" .. cmd .. \" \u0026\")\nend\n\n-- use four finger swipe to switch workspace\nlocal current_id, threshold\nSwipe:start(4, function(direction, distance, id)\n  if id == current_id then\n    if distance \u003e threshold then\n      threshold = math.huge -- only trigger once per swipe\n      if direction == \"left\" then\n        aerospaceExec(\"workspace --wrap-around prev\")\n      elseif direction == \"right\" then\n        aerospaceExec(\"workspace --wrap-around next\")\n      end\n    end\n  else\n    current_id = id\n    threshold = 0.1 -- swipe distance \u003e 10% of trackpad\n  end\nend)\n\n```","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1724940245,"nonce":"xJ+zs2Kq2jmxe86MqvpXIn2uVkA=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOJl1IZM6KJjo7zk5srwA"},"target":"0cfbc962228daaa8cdd372d40660519a099dbfe2bb63332295b569f2a930a6a6","message":"@joeonit Here's a working hammerspoon script, using the 'swipe.spoon' module from my previous comment. It works great - it's a four finger swipe to change workspaces.\n\n```lua\nSwipe = hs.loadSpoon(\"Swipe\")\n\nlocal AEROSPACE = \"/opt/homebrew/bin/aerospace\"\n\nfunction aerospaceExec(cmd)\n  os.execute(\"nohup \" .. AEROSPACE .. \" \" .. cmd .. \" \u0026\")\nend\n\n-- use four finger swipe to switch workspace\nlocal current_id, threshold\nSwipe:start(4, function(direction, distance, id)\n  if id == current_id then\n    if distance \u003e threshold then\n      threshold = math.huge -- only trigger once per swipe\n      if direction == \"left\" then\n        aerospaceExec(\"workspace --wrap-around prev\")\n      elseif direction == \"right\" then\n        aerospaceExec(\"workspace --wrap-around next\")\n      en